---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Danny Peled <Danny.Peled@keshet-tv.com>
Date: Wed, 30 Jun 2021 at 16:15
Subject: Stardom Ventures - update regarding closing and third amended and
restated LPA
To: danny@kdc.fund <danny@kdc.fund>
Cc: Aviran Tovim <Aviran.Tovim@keshet-tv.com>, Tal Dror Schwimmer <
drort@herzoglaw.co.il>


Dear Investors,

I am very pleased to notify you of holding the final closing of KDC Media
Fund, LP (the "*Fund*") today, June 30, 2021, having raised an aggregate
amount of more than *USD 65 million in commitments*.

In connection with the closing, please find attached a counter-signature of
the general partner of the Fund on your subscription.

I want to take this opportunity to thank you personally for putting your
trust in us and being our partners.

Please note that the following comments and requests of the anchor
investors of the Fund that were admitted to the Fund at the final closing
date, we have agreed to make several amendments to the Second Amended and
Restated Limited Partnership Agreement of the Fund (the "*LPA*"), which
include mainly the addition of a no-fault liquidation clause and a no veto
right to any one limited partner clause, lowering the threshold for
liquidation due to a Cause Event, imposing further limitations on the
exculpation and indemnification of covered persons and limiting the voting
power of associated persons of the General Partner of the Fund.

All these changes are favorable to the limited partners.

Accordingly, please find attached clean and marked copies of the amended
LPA for your records, as executed by the general partner in accordance with
Section 13.1.1 of the LPA.

Within the upcoming weeks we will distribute the dividends from previous
exits of the fund.

Yours sincerely,

Danny



